          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Total neutron cross-section of D2O at 20 degrees-C",
                "between 0.0005 and 10 eV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "EXP-YEAR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                1973
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Pulsed 25 MeV Linac.",
                "The electron target was a lead cylinder (d=5 cm,",
                "h=5 cm) located inside the moderator which was a",
                "paraffin cylinder (d=19 cm, h=19 cm). The bottom of a",
                "hole (d=8 cm, h=9 cm) cut into the paraffin, acted as",
                "neutron source. This assembly was cooled with liquid",
                "nitrogen in order to increase the number of low energy",
                "neutrons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The sample containers were cylinders with glass walls",
                "allowing D2O thicknesses of 1.0, 1.4 and 1.8 cm  at",
                "0.1% of accuracy."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Transmission method with pulsed neutron time-of-",
                "flight technique. The sample changer was placed 8.40 m",
                "from the neutron source and had the following positions",
                "  1. D2O sample.",
                "  2. Air filled container identical with that of the",
                "     sample.",
                "  3. A filter opaque to thermal neutrons (a 7 cm thick",
                "     block of paraffin) + an air filled container as",
                "     above.",
                "  4. A filter opaque to thermal neutrons and source",
                "     gamma rays comprised of item 3 above plus a 10 cm",
                "     thick lead brick.",
                "Each run consisted of 12 cycles of the sample changer",
                "and 20 runs were performed with each of the 3 samples."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GLASD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 12.5 cm in diameter by 1.27 cm thick Li-6 glass",
                "scintillator coupled to an EMI-9618R photomultiplier."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
